{:proof/problem-id "apm-a96J06", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (the polynomial \\(p(z)=z+\\sum_{n=2}^N c_n z^n\\), the radius \\(r\\), and the desired \\(\\zeta\\) all appear) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (the Lean target only asserts existence of \\(\\zeta\\) after the nontrivial-coefficient hypothesis) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (showing that such polynomials expand every disk is a standard complex-analysis fact) · notes: the helper lemma is a precise Schwarz-lemma statement for self-maps of the unit disk, which is exactly the bridge needed in the proof.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Show any polynomial of the form p(z)=z+Σ_{n≥2} c_n z^n expands some point in every disk.\"\n :terms [{:name \"normalization\"\n          :meaning \"Scale the disk of radius r to the unit disk via q(z)=p(rz)/r.\"\n          :needed-because \"Lets us apply Schwarz’s lemma on the unit disk.\"}\n         {:name \"Schwarz lemma\"\n          :meaning \"Maps of the unit disk fixing 0 with |q(z)|≤|z| must be rotations; higher coefficients vanish.\"\n          :needed-because \"Gives the contradiction when a higher coefficient is nonzero.\"}\n         {:name \"contradiction setup\"\n          :meaning \"Assume |p(z)|≤r on the disk |z|≤r and derive properties of q.\"\n          :needed-because \"Allows us to negate the desired conclusion.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"Normalization of the disk\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 normalization\"\n             :why-this-now \"Reduce the general r>0 case to a self-map of the unit disk.\"\n             :lean-target \"normalize_polynomial_unit_disk\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Scaling polynomials is straightforward in Mathlib.\"}\n            {:id :s2\n             :formal-dependency \"Schwarz lemma\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 contradiction setup\"\n             :why-this-now \"Conclude that the normalized map must be a rotation, forcing coefficients to vanish.\"\n             :lean-target \"schwarz_contradiction\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Schwarz lemma already exists for holomorphic functions.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done :stage2 :done :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"Any polynomial p(z)=z+Σ_{n≥2} c_n z^n with c_N ≠ 0 expands every disk: ∀ r>0, ∃|ζ|<r with |p(ζ)|>r.\"\n             :formal-name \"polynomial_expands_disk\"\n             :formal-target \"∀ {N : ℕ} {c : ℕ → ℂ} (hN : c N ≠ 0)\n                 (p : ℂ → ℂ), p = fun z => z + ∑_{n=2}^N c n * z^n → ∀ r > 0, ∃ ζ, |ζ| < r ∧ r < |p ζ|\"\n             :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                            :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                            :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                            :notes \"Direct translation of the exam problem.\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"polynomial_expands_disk\"\n              :formal-statement \"(see formal-target)\"\n              :informal-clause \"Main theorem from the prompt.\"\n              :role :main-theorem}\n             {:formal-name \"schwarz_contradiction\"\n              :formal-statement \"If an analytic self-map of the unit disk fixes 0 and has derivative 1 at 0, it is the identity.\"\n              :informal-clause \"Used to contradict the presence of a higher-degree term.\"\n              :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\n**Why it’s hard.** The statement is geometric (“every disk is expanded somewhere”), so it’s tempting to juggle coefficient inequalities. The right approach is analytic: rescale to the unit disk and apply Schwarz’s lemma. Without that normalization step, it’s unclear how to use holomorphic rigidity.\n\n**Key insight.** Suppose the disk \\(|z|<r\\) were mapped inside itself. Scale to the unit disk via \\(q(w)=p(rw)/r\\). Now \\(q:\\mathbb D\\to\\mathbb D\\) is holomorphic, fixes 0, and \\(q'(0)=1\\). Schwarz’s lemma then forces \\(q(w)=e^{i\\theta} w\\). But \\(q\\) contains a nonzero higher-order term (coming from \\(c_N\\ne 0\\)), contradicting Schwarz’s conclusion. Hence every disk must contain a point \\(\\zeta\\) with \\(|p(\\zeta)|>r\\).\n\n**Complete proof.**\n1. Assume, for contradiction, that some \\(r>0\\) satisfies \\(|p(z)|\\le r\\) whenever \\(|z|\\le r\\).\n2. Define \\(q(w)=p(rw)/r = w + \\sum_{n=2}^N c_n r^{n-1} w^n\\). Then \\(q\\) is analytic on \\(\\mathbb D\\), \\(q(0)=0\\), \\(q'(0)=1\\), and \\(|q(w)| \\le 1\\) for \\(|w|\\le 1\\).\n3. Schwarz’s lemma implies \\(|q(w)|\\le |w|\\) and \\(|q'(0)|\\le 1\\); equality at the derivative forces \\(q(w)=e^{i\\theta} w\\).\n4. Comparing coefficients shows all higher-order coefficients vanish—contradicting \\(c_N\\ne 0\\). Therefore the assumption is false, proving that for every \\(r>0\\) there exists \\(|\\zeta|<r\\) with \\(|p(\\zeta)|>r\\).\n\n**Lean 4 formalization.**\n- Main target (`formal-alignment.edn`): `polynomial_expands_disk`, expressing the exact claim.\n- Helper lemma: `schwarz_contradiction`, i.e., Schwarz’s rigidity when \\(q(0)=0\\) and \\(q'(0)=1\\).\n- Plan (`proof-plan.edn`): normalize the disk, apply Schwarz, reach a coefficient contradiction. Stage 3 is still in progress—the normalization lemma plus Schwarz’s rigidity need to be wired into `Main.lean`, but Mathlib already provides the Schwarz-lemma machinery. No `sorry`s yet.\n\n**What connects.** This is a concrete instance of the Open Mapping Theorem + Schwarz rigidity: non-linear holomorphic self-maps of a disk fixing the center can’t have derivative 1. The same idea shows up in the classification of automorphisms of the disk and other rigidity results.\n\n_All required artifacts are populated in `/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J06/apm-v2-a96J06-1775003321530/` (see `execute.md`, `proof-plan.edn`, `formal-alignment.edn`, and `changelog.edn`). Stage 3 remains marked “in progress” until the Lean code is written._", :proof/extraction {:phases {}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :partial, :phase-count 0, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :proof/frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J06/Apm_v2_a96J06_1775003321530", :frame/id "apm-v2-a96J06-1775003321530", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T00:28:41.552555Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.A96J06.Apm_v2_a96J06_1775003321530", :proof/problem-id "a96J06", :workspace/schema "proof-frame-workspace.v1", :frame/workspace-root "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J06/apm-v2-a96J06-1775003321530", :artifacts {:proof-plan "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J06/apm-v2-a96J06-1775003321530/proof-plan.edn", :formal-alignment "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J06/apm-v2-a96J06-1775003321530/formal-alignment.edn", :changelog "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J06/apm-v2-a96J06-1775003321530/changelog.edn", :execute-notes "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J06/apm-v2-a96J06-1775003321530/execute.md", :workspace-readme "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J06/apm-v2-a96J06-1775003321530/README.md", :workspace-metadata "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J06/apm-v2-a96J06-1775003321530/workspace.json", :lean-main "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J06/Apm_v2_a96J06_1775003321530/Main.lean", :lean-scratch "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J06/Apm_v2_a96J06_1775003321530/Scratch.lean"}}, :proof/artifacts ["/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J06/Apm_v2_a96J06_1775003321530/Main.lean" "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J06/Apm_v2_a96J06_1775003321530/Scratch.lean"], :proof/elapsed-ms 71134}